Title: Evaporation of near-extremal Reissner-Nordstrom black holes
Authors: Alessandro Fabbri, Diego J. Navarro and Jose Navarro-Salas
Comments: LaTeX file, 4 pages, 2 figures. Final version, to appear in Phys.
  Rev. Lett
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 85 (2000) 2434-2437
\\
  The formation of near-extremal Reissner-Nordstrom black holes in the S-wave
approximation can be described, near the event horizon, by an effective
solvable model. The corresponding one-loop quantum theory remains solvable and
allows to follow analytically the evaporation process which is shown to require
an infinite amount of time.
